The paper deals with recommendation systems, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) communities. The paper also discusses the use of deep sequence-based models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to the social impact (cs.SI) of recommendation systems.
